Bâr Maenath can be found in the western reaches of the Circle of Death.\n\nYou have encountered a number of enslaved Stout-axes in Bâr Maenath and should free them.
You have freed many of the Stout-axes enslaved by the forces of Minas Morgul. Unlike some of their more combative brethren in Mordor, these Stout-axes welcomed the aid of Gondor and its allies.
Once servants to the Witch-king of Angmar, the Stout-axes now serve the will of Gothmog in Minas Morgul.
You have done well to free many of your lost kindred from Minas Morgul. Although they seem to possess a sickly pallor, you hope it will fade in time as they depart the unhappy lands of Mordor.
You have freed many of the enslaved Stout-axes in Bâr Maenath.
